<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-16T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-16T04:00:00-05:00" n="5" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/2732</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-16T10:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 16, 1917, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 17, 7.30
                                a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2055. Your 616, May 29. Organization completed as outlined my 991, June
                            2. Name “American Prisoners Central Committee.”<note n="1" xml:id="d5fn1">After amalgamation with the Red Cross, the name of
                                the organization was changed, in August, to “American Red
                                Cross–Central Committee for American Prisoners.”</note> Suggest that
                            instructions be issued to all officers and men, military and naval, sent
                            abroad, in case of capture immediately to communicate with committee
                            here.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>